<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,222,248]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The species is easily recognized superficially by its white forewing with black markings formed by raised scales. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Bidzilya, 2021" authorityName="Bidzilya" authorityYear="2021" box="[484,589,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erexita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[484,589,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. erexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[596,685,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[596,685,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but in 
<taxonomicName authority="Bidzilya, 2021" authorityName="Bidzilya" authorityYear="2021" box="[771,928,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="admirabilis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[771,928,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. admirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[935,1025,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[935,1025,259,285]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the ground colour of the forewing is white rather than light brown, and the black markings are more well defined. The male genitalia differ from those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bidzilya, 2021" authorityName="Bidzilya" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,256,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erexita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,256,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. erexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[263,352,331,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[263,352,331,357]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in having a longer sacculus and shorter vincular process (for additional details, see the diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bidzilya, 2021" authorityName="Bidzilya" authorityYear="2021" box="[182,287,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erexita" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[182,287,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">S. erexita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[293,383,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[293,383,367,393]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,420,402,428]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Description. Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[436,570,402,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 51–60" captionStartId="53.[151,264,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[298,1288,181,1760]" captionTargetId="figure-16@53.[298,1288,181,1768]" captionTargetPageId="53" captionText="FIGURES 51–60. Scrobipalpa spp., adults. 51. S. staudei sp. nov., South Africa, Magaliesburg, HT, male (gen. slide 3/19, OB). 52–54. S. obsoletella, South Africa. 52. Vredental, female (gen. slide 37/13, OB). 53. Vredental, male, HT of hospes (gen. slide K. Sattler 287a). 54. South Africa, Port Elizabeth, male, HT of xylochroa. 55. S. afromontana sp. nov., Kenya, Rutundu Track, HT, male (gen. slide DJLA 1419). 56. S. erexita sp. nov., South Africa, 50 km NE Bitterfontein, HT, female (gen. slide 154/17, OB). 57, 58. S. admirabilis sp. nov., Namibia, Fischriver, Gondwana Canyon Lodge. 57. HT, male (gen. slide 317/20, OB). 58. PT, male (gen. slide 164/12, OB). 59, 60. S. griseata sp. nov., South Africa, Petersburg. 59. HT, male (gen. slide 15/13, OB). 60. PT, male. Scale bar = wingspan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5712547" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5712547/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Figs 57, 58</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 9.1–9.4 mm. Head and thorax white, tegulae white with browntipped scales at base; labial palpus white with brown basal and medial rings, inner surface white; scape brown, flagellum brown with broad white rings; forewing white, black spots at base and on 1/3 of costal margin, two small black spots with yellow scales between them at base of wing at mid-width, black diffuse spot formed by weakly raised scales from 1/3 to 1/2 length at mid-width, black dash on 2/3 of costal margin, black patch of irregular shape, suffused with light brown from 2/3 of dorsum to mid-width, subapical area distinctly mottled with black and light brown raised scales, apical black streak narrow, cilia with short and long, black-tipped, white scales; hind wing and cilia white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,373,690,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[392,493,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 123–128" captionStartId="62.[151,264,1866,1890]" captionTargetBox="[211,1377,195,1822]" captionTargetId="figure-24@62.[195,1392,181,1842]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="FIGURES 123–128. Scrobipalpa spp., male genitalia. 123–125. S. obsoletella, South Africa. 123. Rocherpan N.R (gen. slide 137/12, OB). 124. Vredendal (gen. slide 39/13, OB). 125. Port Elizabeth, PT of xylochroa (gen. slide 247/12, OB). 126. S. afromontana sp. nov., Kenya, Rutundu Track, HT (gen. slide DJLA No. 1419). 127. S. erexita sp. nov., South Africa, Soebatsfontein, PT (gen. slide g. 5146). 128. S. admirabilis sp. nov., Namibia, Fischriver, Gondwana Canyon Lodge, HT (gen. slide 317/20, OB)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5712576" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5712576/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 128</figureCitation>
). Uncus elongate, weakly tapered in distal half; gnathos hook short, wide, weakly curved; tegumen moderately broad, anterior margin with rounded medial emargination extending to about 1/3 length of tegumen; valva slender, weakly widened apically, extending to apex of uncus; sacculus twice as broad as and about 1/2 length of valva, turned inwards, with pointed, inward-curved tip, separated from vincular process by broadly rounded gap; vinculum moderately broad, with deep triangular medial emargination; vincular process short, subtriangular, with outwardly turned pointed tip; saccus wide at base, abruptly narrowed after 1/3, apex pointed, extending beyond top of pedunculus; distal portion of phallus straight, apex slightly inflated, with distinct transversal apical hook, caecum strongly swollen, slightly shorter than distal portion of phallus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" box="[199,528,978,1005]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,978,1005]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1014,1040]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Biology.</emphasis>
Host plant unknown. The adults were recorded in October and April in Dwarf Shrub Savanna (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 197–202" captionStartId="82.[151,264,1644,1668]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,181,1620]" captionTargetId="figure-24@82.[156,1432,181,1620]" captionTargetPageId="82" captionText="FIGURES 197–202. Habitats. 197. Biota observatory Karios, Namibia. Habitats of S. admirabilis sp. nov. (photo W. Mey). 198–202.Asante-Sana, South Africa. Habitats of S. ochroxantha sp. nov., S. typica sp. nov., S. griseata sp. nov., S. ochracea sp. nov., S. asantesana sp. nov., S. geomicta, S. portosanctana. 198. View from Waterkloof valley. 199. Farm cottage, Petersburg. Collection site of S. griseata sp. nov., S. asantesana sp. nov., S. portosanctana. 200–201. Environs of Farm cottage, Petersburg. 202. Environs of Glen Haven." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5712650" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5712650/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 197</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
