<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,1185]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1123,1149]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin “ 
<emphasis box="[849,972,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">admirabile</emphasis>
”—admirable, wonderful—and alludes to the conspicuous forewing pattern of the species, in comparison to most other species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Huemer &amp; Karsholt" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[1136,1272,1159,1185]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Scrobipalpa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1136,1272,1159,1185]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Scrobipalpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
